T1  - The Effect of State Policies on the Location of Manufacturing: Evidence from State Borders
AU  - Holmes, Thomas J.
Y1  - 1998/08/01
PY  - 1998
DA  - 1998/08/01
N1  - doi: 10.1086/250026
DO  - 10.1086/250026
T2  - Journal of Political Economy
JF  - Journal of Political Economy
SP  - 667
EP  - 705
VL  - 106
IS  - 4
PB  - The University of Chicago Press
N2  - This paper provides new evidence that state policies play a role in the location of industry. The paper classifies a state as probusiness if it has a right?to?work law and antibusiness if it does not. The paper finds that, on average, there is a large, abrupt increase in manufacturing activity when one crosses a state border from an antibusiness state into a probusiness state.
AB  - This paper provides new evidence that state policies play a role in the location of industry. The paper classifies a state as probusiness if it has a right?to?work law and antibusiness if it does not. The paper finds that, on average, there is a large, abrupt increase in manufacturing activity when one crosses a state border from an antibusiness state into a probusiness state.
SN  - 0022-3808
M3  - doi: 10.1086/250026
UR  - https://doi.org/10.1086/250026
Y2  - 2024/03/22
