SP  - 854
EP  - 859
VL  - 106
IS  - 4
PB  - The University of Chicago Press
N2  - In 1797 Johann Wolfgang von Goethe sold a manuscript through a second?price auction. We investigate Goethe's motivation in the context of the late eighteenth century's book market and relate it to modern auction theory.
AB  - In 1797 Johann Wolfgang von Goethe sold a manuscript through a second?price auction. We investigate Goethe's motivation in the context of the late eighteenth century's book market and relate it to modern auction theory.
SN  - 0022-3808
M3  - doi: 10.1086/250032
UR  - https://doi.org/10.1086/250032
Y2  - 2024/03/22
